title: Championship Chatter: Aharon Eggleston
text:
CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
“There was a lot of clutch hitting, and our pitching staff was phenomenal. I’d like to know what our pitchers did with runners in scoring position. Long Island and Southern Maryland got guys in scoring position in big situations in both series, and our pitchers shut them down both times. They kept us in it, and we knew that. I think with the pitching, we knew there was no pressure on the hitters and we knew that we were always going to be in the game.” 
“At the end of the year, we finally get to celebrate. We’ve battled all year, and the last two years we came up short with what we thought was the best team in the league. Finally, we’re the best team in the league this year, and we were able to win the last game of the year.”
